Police in Kieni West, Nyeri county, are holding a 25-year-old woman who allegedly stabbed to death her husband. Kawira is said to have stabbed Joseph Gitaru, 37, two times on the chest on Wednesday.She covered the body with a blanket and left it outside the house. Kawira tried to escape, leaving behind her seven-month-old baby, but police arrested her.Area police boss John Kemboi said the couple quarrelled earlier at a local bar, where they were drinking.He said they are still looking for the murder weapon.Kemboi said the woman will face murder charges once investigations are complete.